<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/support/">Support</a> / <a href="/support/voice/">Voice</a> / <a href="/support/voice/firewall/">Firewall</a> / Netgear</p>
<h1>Disable SIP ALG on Netgear routers.</h1>
<p class="lede">Netgear ships SIP ALG enabled on most Nighthawk and Orbi consumer firmware. The toggle is buried under WAN Setup; disable it before placing production traffic.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Steps (Nighthawk / Orbi)</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Sign in to the router admin UI: <code>http://www.routerlogin.net</code> or <code>http://192.168.1.1</code>.</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Advanced</strong> in the top tab bar.</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Setup → WAN Setup</strong>.</li>
		<li>Tick <strong>Disable SIP ALG</strong>.</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>. The router reboots automatically on some firmware revisions; otherwise reboot manually under <strong>Advanced → Administration → Reboot</strong>.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Steps (ProSAFE / business)</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Sign in to the firewall management UI.</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Security → Application Level Gateway</strong>.</li>
		<li>Untick <strong>SIP</strong>.</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>UDP NAT timeout</h2>
	<p>Netgear consumer firmware doesn't expose a UDP conntrack timeout. If you see registration drops between calls, set each device's SIP REGISTER interval to 360 seconds with NAT keepalive at 30 seconds. ProSAFE business firmware exposes session timeouts under <strong>Security → Schedule Profile</strong>; raise UDP idle timeout to 600 s for SIP traffic if your model supports it.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Verify</h2>
	<p>Place a test call. If audio is bidirectional for the full call duration including past 30 minutes, ALG is no longer in the path. Wait 5–10 minutes idle, then place an inbound test call to confirm registration is still alive.</p>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="netgear-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="netgear-cta-heading">Toggle missing on your firmware?</h2>
	<p>Some older Netgear consumer firmware doesn't expose the SIP ALG toggle. Update to the latest firmware revision; contact VoiceTel engineering if your model is end-of-life.</p>
